# Vercel Speed Insights Installation Report

## Summary
Successfully installed and configured Vercel Speed Insights for the porta-moneta Next.js application.

## Changes Made

### 1. Package Installation
- Installed `@vercel/speed-insights` package version ^1.1.0
- Updated package.json to include the new dependency
- Updated package-lock.json with the complete dependency tree

### 2. Code Integration (app/layout.tsx)
- Added import statement: `import { SpeedInsights } from "@vercel/speed-insights/next";`
- Added `<SpeedInsights />` component to the root layout, placed after the existing `<Analytics />` component
- Follows the official Vercel documentation for Next.js 13.5+ projects

## Implementation Details

The implementation follows the official Vercel Speed Insights quickstart guide for Next.js applications:
- Used the Next.js-specific import path (`@vercel/speed-insights/next`)
- Placed the component in the root layout for global tracking
- Positioned alongside the existing Vercel Analytics component for consistent monitoring setup

## Framework Compatibility
- Project uses Next.js 15.5.6 (fully compatible with Speed Insights)
- Integrated seamlessly with existing Vercel Analytics setup
- No conflicts with existing components or providers

## Verification Completed
✅ Build completed successfully with no errors
✅ Linter passed with no new warnings or errors
✅ TypeScript compilation successful
✅ All static pages generated correctly
✅ Lock files properly updated

## Files Modified
1. **app/layout.tsx** - Added SpeedInsights component and import
2. **package.json** - Added @vercel/speed-insights dependency
